Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 9
Edition:
Quote: <i>all around the pig's arse there is pork</i> indicating acceptance, resignation, fatalism, in regard to a fait accompli, such as an opponent's winning snooker break.
